# Normalize line endings across all platforms.
#
# `text=auto`  — git decides per file whether it's text (binaries are
#                auto-detected and left untouched).
# `eol=lf`     — text files are stored AND checked out as LF, on every OS.
#                This overrides each machine's core.autocrlf, so Windows
#                working copies stop drifting to CRLF (which is what caused
#                the LF→CRLF diff churn) and shell scripts like .husky/*
#                stay LF-safe. The app deploys to Linux, so LF is the
#                correct canonical form.
* text=auto eol=lf
